With its sporty casual and elegant look, the Aquanaut is a favorite amongst international travelers, constantly on-the-go.

The new Aquanaut Luce Travel Time presents itself as a true travel companion.

It features two hour hands – one pierced for home time, the other solid for local time.

When changing time zones, the hour hand for local time may be set forwards or backwards by increments of one hour using the crown.

#PatekTime #Aquanaut #AquanautLuce

node.text:
The new Ref. 5236 In-line Perpetual Calendar opens up a new chapter in the storied history of Patek Philippe calendar timepieces, with the addition of a totally new perpetual calendar wristwatch with an innovative patented one-line display that displays the day, the date, and the month on a single line. 

While seemingly simple, the in-line display presented a highly complex technical challenge and the development of a new movement (caliber 31-260 PS QL) for which three patent applications have been filed.  

#PatekPhilippe #PerpetualCalendar #PatekTime

node.text:
The new Ref. 5236 In-line Perpetual Calendar houses the new self-winding movement caliber 31-260 PS QL. PS for ‘petite seconde’ [subsidiary seconds] and QL for ‘quantième perpétuel en ligne’ [in-line perpetual calendar]). The seemingly simple in-line display presented a highly complex technical challenge and development of three patented innovations.

The movement consists of 503 parts, 298 of which are dedicated to the perpetual calendar function. In the assembly process, a ‘test’ dial is used to ensure the optimal functionality of the in-line display.

#PatekPhilippe #PerpetualCalendar #PatekTime

With the introduction of these new timepieces, Patek Philippe creates an eclectic bouquet of novelties - ranging from the much awaited, casual elegant Nautilus collection, new additions to the timelessly elegant Calatrava collection, a totally new Grand Complication and an addition to the ingenious patented Annual Calendar collection.
 
The introduction of these new references reflect the Manufacture’s extensive mastery of technical complexity, without sacrificing a perfect aesthetic.

“If you want to preserve your independence, you must have a fantastic product, and to have a fantastic product, you have to control the quality that goes inside. To do that, you have to do it yourself. We have been evolving in terms of quantity, in terms of complexity, and we needed more space, more tools, more people, more machines.

This is why we decided at one point, in 2013, to think about the future of Patek Philippe, by having a new building.”

Thierry Stern, President, Patek Philippe

node.text: Trace back the extraordinary heritage of the Gondolo; from its Brazilian origins in the late 1800s right through to today’s men’s and ladies Art Deco-inspired collection.

With its modern, unexpected design and a character all its own, the Aquanaut created a sensation since its launch in 1997.

Patek Philippe revisits the original Aquanaut Luce sporty chic design first launched in 2004 with a new generation of quartz-powered models in steel and a self-winding model in rose gold.

The Manufacture is also introducing the first additional function to join the Aquanaut Luce collection: the Travel Time dual time zone.

node.text:
Patek Philippe is giving fresh allure to its quartz-driven Aquanaut Luce models in steel, a shining example of contemporary sportive chic.

The new reference 5267/200 in steel comes with matching dial and strap in a choice of three colors: eternally elegant black, a very feminine matt white, and an audacious khaki green.

The dials and straps featuring the embossed Aquanaut decor are remarkable for their blend of sportiness and refinement.

The steel case is adorned with a polished and satin-brushed finishes. The bezel is lit by a circle of 48 brilliant-cut Top Wesselton Pure diamonds.

#PatekTime #AquanautLuce #Aquanaut

Did you know the Aquanaut Luce owes its name to the circle of diamonds illuminating its bezel ?

node.text:
With its sporty casual and elegant look, the Aquanaut is a favorite amongst international travelers, constantly on-the-go.

The new Aquanaut Luce Travel Time presents itself as a true travel companion.

It features two hour hands – one pierced for home time, the other solid for local time.

When changing time zones, the hour hand for local time may be set forwards or backwards by increments of one hour using the crown.

#PatekTime #Aquanaut #AquanautLuce

Patek Philippe introduces the Aquanaut Luce Automatic.

The sapphire-crystal caseback of this rose gold model – it has a diameter of 38.8 mm and is water-resistant to 120 meters – reveals the architecture and refined finissage of the self-winding caliber 26-330 S C.

It was optimized with various innovations, two of which are patented. A stop-seconds mechanism blocks the balance when the crown is pulled, thus enabling the time to be set with one-second accuracy.

The integrated matt-white strap emphasizes the visual harmony of the overall design.

#PatekTime #Aquanaut #AquanautLuce

The Aquanaut Luce collection is the ideal companion for a delightful summer.

Light as its diamond-setting, supple as its strap, the collection evokes a sense of effortless casual chic, as easy as a summer breeze.

#PatekTime #Aquanaut #AquanautLuce

node.text:
The new Aquanaut Luce collection features three main new characteristics contributing to its audacious and elegant design.

The sporty chic look of Aquanaut Luce has been revisited in a larger diameter (38.8 mm) fitted with a new integrated strap.

The strap is a feature in its own right. It is a made of a high-tech water-resistant composite material that is supple, comfortable and pleasant to touch and noted for its extreme resistance to traction, wear, salt water and ultraviolet radiation.

The patented fold-over clasp is secured by four independent catches, adapted to partner the most active lifestyles.

#PatekTime #Aquanaut #AquanautLuce

Rituals celebrates the personal routines of the modern woman.

Patek Philippe effortlessly accompanies these moments, adding beauty and elegance to every moment of her life.

In this new ritual, it is all about taking time to relax on vacation at golden hour.

#PatekTime #Aquanaut #AquanautLuce
